Koor Heads for Seven-Week High as Discount Investment Raises Bid

-- B y   S u s a n   L e r n e r
-- 
2011-10-05T08:27:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-05/koor-heads-for-seven-week-high-as-discount-investment-raises-bid.html
Koor Industries Ltd. (KOR)  headed for the
highest close since Aug. 15 after  Discount Investment Corp. (DISI) 
raised its offer for 3.3 million shares of the holding company
from 35 shekels a share to 38.5 shekels.  Koor shares rose 7.7 percent to 37.60 shekels at 10:12 a.m.
in Tel Aviv. Discount shares increased 3.2 percent to 31.99
shekels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Susan Lerner in Jerusalem at 
 slerner2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  